Program: Outlook
Title: 21/01/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00d1xj9
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 24 Jan 2011
DR ENRIQUE STEIGER The surgeon with two very different kinds of patients: the jet-set in search of the body beautiful and people fighting for their lives in the world's worst conflict zones. He tells us about his remarkable double life. BLIND ARTIST The British painter Sargy Mann, now in his seventies, was diagnosed with cataracts as a young man and began to lose his sight. He finally went totally blind but continued to paint. He tells Outlook how going blind allowed him to produce the best work of his life. Show less